so possible to infer\nKepler-63 differential rotation from the presence of spots at different\nlatitudes. This star was found to rotate almost rigidly with a period of 5.400d\nand relative shear close to 0.01% for latitudes less than 34{\\deg}, whereas the\nhigh latitudes do not follow a well behaved pattern.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 20 Nov 2019 01:36:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-11"}
