ncontext of a recently introduced model for $Chlamydomonas$ phototaxis, an\nadaptive response of the peripheral cells alone leads to photo-reorientation of\nthe entire colony. The analysis also highlights the importance of local\nvariations in flagellar beat dynamics within a given colony, which can lead to\nenhanced reorientation dynamics.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 20 Nov 2019 11:32:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-04"}
